{"questionId":"33010144","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the roots of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Give these roots in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mi>t</mi></msqrt></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to solve&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><br><br></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br><br></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br><br></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; and <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33010144","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.2ai","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine the roots of x2+4x+1=0. Give these roots in the form s±t, where s∈ℤ and t∈ℤ+.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}